gomodel:SYNGO_1930  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Cbln1 and the NTD of GluD2 cooperatively induce synaptogenesis in vitro and in vivo\"\nPresynapse formation onto GluD2 expressing HEK cells is perturbed in Cbln1 KO neurons. Effect is absent when truncated versions of GluD2 are used. Synapse formation is restored in Cbln1 KO mice after injection of HA-Cbln1.\n\nFig.3: \"Cbln1 is a direct presynaptic organizer\". Experimental description: 20/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of mouse species\n- Cell culures were of mouse species: \"Mixed cerebellar cultures were prepared from embryonic day 17 to day-of-birth ICR, GluD2-null (ho5J) or cbln1-null mice \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1930" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

